CmsHccV28PatientsRegistryDataMart

CmsHccV28PatientsRegistryDataMart is loaded from DM_CMS_HCC_V28, DM_CMS_HCC_V28_2 and DM_CMS_HCC_V28_3. These are Clarity data mart tables that store information related to the CMS-HCC Registry metrics. Each row represents metric data for a patient for a specific timespan. This table consolidates data about the applicability of hierarchical conditions categories (HCCs), most recent related diagnosis information, and whether or not the patient requires a calendar year refresh for each applicable HCC. For each HCC category, this information is consolidated into the corresponding EpicStatus column. Only patients that meet specific inclusion criteria have information stored in this table.

Properties

Reporting table name
dbo.CmsHccV28PatientsRegistryDataMart
Granularity

  2. PatientDim
  3. PatientDimSourceData

    Hcc1EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the CMS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: HIV/AIDS (83600)

    Properties

    Data type
    number
    SQL Server data type
    numeric(2,0)
    Allows null
    Yes
    •

    Data Lineage for Each Package

    CMS-HCC V28 Patients Load
    Hcc1EpicStatus
    DM_CMS_HCC_V28.HIV_AIDS_CM

The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Opportunistic Infections (83602)

    DM_CMS_HCC_V28.DIAB_WITH_GLYCEM_NO_COMP_DT

    Hcc38EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the CMS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Diabetes with Glycemic, Unspecified, or No Complications (83613)

The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Intestine Transplant Status/Complications (83623)

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Acquired Hemolytic, Aplastic, and Sideroblastic Anemias (83633)

    Hcc138LastDiagnosisDate
    DM_CMS_HCC_V28.DRG_USE_DIS_UNCMP_EXCP_CAN_DT

    Hcc138EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the CMS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Drug Use Disorder, Mild, Uncomplicated, Except Cannabis (83644)

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis and Other Motor Neuron Disease, Spinal Muscular Atrophy (83654)

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Seizure Disorders and Convulsions (83664)

    CMS-HCC V28 Patients Load
    Hcc227LastDiagnosisDate
    DM_CMS_HCC_V28_2.CARDIOMYOPATHY_MYOCARDITIS_DT

    Hcc227EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the CMS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Cardiomyopathy/Myocarditis (83677)

    Data type

    SQL Server data type

    Allows null

    The status of the CMS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Deep Vein Thrombosis and Pulmonary Embolism (83687)

The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Chronic Kidney Disease, Stage 5 (83697)

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: CMS-HCC V28: Pemphigus, Pemphigoid, and Other Specified Autoimmune Skin Disorders (83737)

    tinyint
    Allows null
    No
    Default value
    0
